headline: RTX's Pratt & Whitney awarded $1.6 billion F135 sustainment contract
summary: Pratt & Whitney, an RTX (NYSE: RTX) business, has been awarded a $1.6 billion undefinitized contract action for sustainment of F135 engines, which power all three variants of the F-35 Lightning II, the world's most advanced fighter aircraft.
